Were you able to squeeze the reading of this sentence into your tight schedule, and to divine its meaning—that it would terminate Trump’s recently declared national emergency?
Then you, reader, have gotten much farther along in your review process than a number of Senate Republicans.
Until they have to take that vote, many Senate Republicans would prefer to hold their votes close to the chest.
“[Trump] has a justification where he’s said, ‘I’m declaring this a national emergency,’ and then we’re waiting for the legal justification and the line items,” Lankford said.